input: Bob is cold. Bob is nice. Dave is blue. Dave is nice. Dave is quiet. Fiona is rough. Fiona is young. Gary is blue. Gary is cold. Gary is nice. Gary is quiet. Gary is red. Gary is rough. Gary is young. All red people are blue. If Fiona is nice then Fiona is blue. If Fiona is blue then Fiona is red. If someone is young then they are quiet. Cold, quiet people are nice. Quiet, young people are cold. If someone is red and rough then they are blue. If someone is red then they are nice. Question: Fiona is not red.?
output:
universe u

constant obj : Type u

constant Bob : obj
constant Dave : obj
constant Fiona : obj
constant Gary : obj

constant Cold : obj → Prop
constant Nice : obj → Prop
constant Blue : obj → Prop
constant Quiet : obj → Prop
constant Rough : obj → Prop
constant Young : obj → Prop
constant Red : obj → Prop

axiom T1 : Cold Bob
axiom T2 : Nice Bob
axiom T3 : Blue Dave
axiom T4 : Nice Dave
axiom T5 : Quiet Dave
axiom T6 : Rough Fiona
axiom T7 : Young Fiona
axiom T8 : Blue Gary
axiom T9 : Cold Gary
axiom T10 : Nice Gary
axiom T11 : Quiet Gary
axiom T12 : Red Gary
axiom T13 : Rough Gary
axiom T14 : Young Gary

axiom R1 : ∀ x : obj, Red x → Blue x
axiom R2 : Nice Fiona → Blue Fiona
axiom R3 : Blue Fiona → Red Fiona
axiom R4 : ∀ x : obj, Young x → Quiet x
axiom R5 : ∀ x : obj, Cold x ∧ Quiet x → Nice x
axiom R6 : ∀ x : obj, Quiet x ∧ Young x → Cold x
axiom R7 : ∀ x : obj, Red x ∧ Rough x → Blue x
axiom R8 : ∀ x : obj, Red x → Nice x

theorem fiona_is_not_red : ¬ Red Fiona :=
begin
  intro H,
  have H1 : Blue Fiona := R1 Fiona H,
  have H2 : Red Fiona := R3 Fiona H1,
  contradiction,
end

-- The answer is True
